              Java, C++, HTML, cybersecurity, hardware, and computer
              fundamentals. A top performer in academics, he scored 6 A*s and 2
              As in his IGCSE 10th-grade finals, and was the topper in Math,
              Computer Science, and Physics in Grade 12. He built his first
              game, multiplayer Hand Cricket, using Python and SQL, which was
              featured in his school's Science Fair, and won a competitive
              coding competition at Oakridge aged 16 - defining moments that led
              him to pursue Computer Science in college.
            </p>
